{{Quote|This was Thrawn's personal base. The databases in the fortress core below us are possibly the most extensive in the galaxy.|[[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Voss Parck/Legends|Voss Parck]] to [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]]|<ref name="Vision of the Future">''[[Vision of the Future]]''</ref>}}
The '''Hand of Thrawn''', known as the '''High Tower''', was the ancient fortress on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Nirauan/Legends|Nirauan]], which served as the [[Capital/Legends|capital]] for the [[Empire of the Hand]]. Its name was due to its five towers, which vaguely resembled an outstretched hand. 

==Description==
===Construction===
It was chosen by [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]] as the center of his efforts in the [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]] to conquer territory for the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and defend it from threats from the galactic fringes or from outside the [[Galaxy/Legends|galaxy]]. It contained a fully equipped command center, library, and a cloning facility in which Thrawn had kept a [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo (clone)|clone of himself]] in stasis. The complex also held an advanced database. It also had a holomap of the galaxy to show sectors that were underneath Thrawn's control.<ref name="Vision of the Future" />

===Defensive Capabilities===
Surrounded by various [[Turbolaser/Legends|turbolaser]] [[Turret/Legends|batteries]], and a hangar bay equipped with a wing of [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighters]], the Hand of Thrawn was highly secured from an attack. Guarded heavily by a garrison of Chiss soldiers, infiltration inside the complex would be pointless.<ref name="Vision of the Future" />

==History==
===Jedi Infiltration===
By [[19 ABY/Legends|19 ABY]], it had become the leading fortress of the [[Empire of the Hand]]. Its garrison, comprised for the most part of [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] troops, was commanded by Imperial officer [[Voss Parck/Legends|Voss Parck]]. [[Soontir Fel/Legends|Soontir Fel]] was also part of the Hand of Thrawn's complement. When [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] disappeared on a mission to track down the source of [[Cloning/Legends|clones]] and [[Nssis-class Clawcraft|mysterious starfighters]] which had recently become active, [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] followed her. Joining with some of the native [[Qom Jha and Qom Qae]], they [[Mission to Nirauan|infiltrated]] the compound. In order to prevent the Hand of Thrawn from turning itself over to [[Bastion/Legends|Bastion]] and the Empire, Mara Jade used a beckon call to drive her ship, ''[[Jade's Fire]]'', into the compound, damaging the main hangar and all remaining ships. Luke and Mara then reentered the compound, where they discovered Thrawn's secret cloning chamber. While battling two sentry droids, the entire chamber flooded, but they were able to escape by forcing Thrawn's cloning cylinder to explode, resulting in the water draining and allowing them to escape. After escaping, Luke discovered that R2-D2 also managed to download an unaltered copy of the [[Caamas Document]].<ref name="Vision of the Future" />

===Pirate attack===
{{Quote|There were two waves of attack. The first came from Jedi spies. The facility was destroyed. We salvaged what we could before other ships arrived, forcing a tactical retreat.|[[Kres'ten'tarthi|Stent]] to [[Jagged Fel]]|<ref name="RSBF">{{GamerCite|7|Red Sky, Blue Flame}}</ref>}}
Following Luke Skywalker and Mara Jade's intervention, the Hand of Thrawn was attacked and looted by the [[Cavrilhu Pirates]] who were involved in some skirmishes with the Jedi and had followed them to Nirauan. Due to the destruction of their defenses by the Jedi, the personnel of the base were forced to evacuate. Fearing that the pirates could have obtained information about the secret Chiss installations in the ruins, [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Kres'ten'tarthi|Stent]] went to the [[Syndic Mitth'raw'nuruodo training academy]] in the [[Rata Nebula/Legends|Rata Nebula]] to prevent a pirate attack.<ref name="RSBF" />

===Refurbishment===
The fortress was eventually renovated and back into service. In [[22 ABY/Legends|22 ABY]], Luke Skywalker and Mara Jade traveled once again to Nirauan after being contacted by Parck from the Hand of Thrawn.<ref name="SQ">''[[Survivor's Quest]]''</ref>

